# Windsurf Rules for tox

You are working on tox, a Python CLI tool for test automation and virtual environment management.

## Language and Style

- Python 3.10+ (minimum supported version)
- ALWAYS start every module with `from __future__ import annotations`
- Use type hints on all function signatures and class attributes
- Line length: 120 characters (ruff enforced)
- Formatter: ruff (preview mode). Linter: ruff with `ALL` rules enabled
- Docstrings: RST format for Sphinx compatibility
- Use `TYPE_CHECKING` guard for imports only needed by type checkers
- First-party imports: `tox` and `tests`

## Project Layout

- Source code: `src/tox/` (src layout, NOT top-level)
- Tests: `tests/` (mirrors src structure)
- Config: `tox.toml` (tox's own config), `pyproject.toml` (build + tools)
- Type stubs: `typestubs/`
- Docs: `docs/` (Sphinx + RST)

## Architecture

- Plugin-based architecture using pluggy. Hooks define all extension points
- Config loaded from tox.toml, tox.ini, pyproject.toml, or setup.cfg via unified loader
- Core abstraction: `ToxEnv` -> `Python` -> `VirtualEnv` hierarchy in `src/tox/tox_env/`
- Session flow: CLI parsing -> config loading -> env selection -> provisioning -> command dispatch
- Commands live in `src/tox/session/cmd/` (run, list, depends, devenv, exec, show-config, etc.)

## Testing

- Framework: pytest with pytest-xdist (parallel execution), pytest-mock, pytest-timeout
- Run tests: `pytest tests/ -n auto` or `tox run -e py`
- Fast iteration: `tox run -e fast` (skips integration/slow tests and coverage)
- Test markers: `@pytest.mark.integration`, `@pytest.mark.slow`
- Coverage minimum: 88%
- Timeout: 30 seconds per test (default)

## Commands

- `tox run -e fix` - lint and format (pre-commit + ruff)
- `tox run -e type` - type check with ty
- `tox run -e docs` - build Sphinx documentation
- `tox run -e pkg_meta` - validate package metadata

## Conventions

- Changelog fragments go in `docs/changelog/{issue}.{type}.rst` (towncrier)
- Fragment types: feature, bugfix, doc, removal, misc
- Config values use lazy evaluation (computed on demand)
- Plugin registration via `[project.entry-points.tox]` in pyproject.toml
- Local plugins can be defined in `toxfile.py`
- Environment variable substitution syntax: `{env:VAR_NAME:default}`

## Do NOT

- Do not use `typing.Optional` or `typing.Union` - use `X | None` and `X | Y` syntax
- Do not add imports outside of `TYPE_CHECKING` blocks unless the import is needed at runtime
- Do not skip the `from __future__ import annotations` import
- Do not write tests without proper isolation (use tmp_path, monkeypatch)
- Do not use `print()` in source code (use logging/report module)
